**Secretary Problem (Optimal Stopping).** Interview $n$ candidates in random order. After each interview you must immediately hire or reject (no recalls). \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Show the optimal strategy is: reject the first $k-1$ candidates, then hire the first who is better than all previously seen.

\item Find the optimal $k$ for large $n$.

\item What is the probability of hiring the best candidate as $n\to\infty$?\end{enumerate}

**Two-Egg Problem: Optimal Floor Testing.** You have 2 eggs and a 100-story building. An egg breaks from floor $F$ or higher. Minimise the worst-case number of drops to find $F$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item If you perform at most $k$ drops total, what is the maximum number of floors you can check?

\item What is the minimum $k$ for a 100-story building?

\item Describe the optimal strategy.\end{enumerate}
